{
  "text": "A Puerto Rican isolate of Schistosoma mansoni was maintained by passage through albino Biomphalaria glabrata snails and infection of 3-5 week-old, female Mesocricetus auratus Golden Syrian hamsters [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Cercariae (infectious larvae) were obtained from infected snails and mechanically transformed into somules as previously described [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . To obtain adult schistosomes, hamsters were euthanized 42-45 days post-infection using an intraperitoneal injection of 50 mg/kg sodium pentobarbital containing 50 U/ml heparin (as an anticoagulant) in a total of 100 μL PBS. Worms were harvested by reverse perfusion of the hepatic portal system [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] in RPMI 1640 medium supplemented with 100 U/ml penicillin and 100 mg/ml streptomycin [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] . Adults were transferred into Basch medium 169 [CITATION_11] supplemented with 100 U/ml penicillin and 100 mg/ml streptomycin. In this medium, parasites were washed three times, allowed to stand for 30-60 min in the presence of 2X amphotericin B (fungizone) and then washed another three times in medium minus fungizone prior to phenotypic screening.",
  "correct_citation": {
